condition.narrative: Finance Agreement :Accounting SoftwareFinancing Agreement Reference II.B.1(b) | Description :The Recipient shall purchase, installand program an accounting software acceptable to the Association and in a manner acceptable to the Association within 2 months ofeffectiveness. | Due Date :28-Dec-2013

Finance Agreement :Administrative, Accounting, and Financial Manual of ProceduresFA 5.01(b) | Description :The Recipient hasadopted the Manual of Procedures for the Project in form and substance acceptable to the Association | Due Date :31-Oct-2013

Finance Agreement :External AuditorsFinancing Agreement Reference II.B.4 | Description :In order to ensure the timely carrying outof the audits, the Recipient shall engage auditors for the purpose, in accordance with the provisions of the FA within 4 months ofeffectiveness. | Due Date :28-Feb-2014

Finance Agreement :Internal AuditorFinancing Agreement Reference I.A.2(c) | Description :The Recipient shall recruit an internalauditor with terms of reference, qualifications and experience satisfactory to the Association within 2 months of effectiveness. |Due Date :28-Dec-2013

Finance Agreement :Monitoring and Evaluation SpecialistFinancing Agreement Reference I.A.2(c) | Description :The Recipient shallrecruit a Monitoring and Evaluation Specialist with terms of reference, qualifications, and experience satisfactory to theAssociation within 6 months of effectiveness. | Due Date :28-Apr-2014

Finance Agreement :Project Coordination UnitFinancing Agreement Reference 5.01(d) | Description :The Recipient has (i) establishedthe Project Coordination Unit and (ii) recruited the following consultants for the PIU: a Project Coordinator, a procurementspecialist, a financial management specialist, and an accountant. | Due Date :31-Oct-2013

Finance Agreement :Project Implementation ManualFinancing Agreement Reference 5.01 (b) | Description :The Recipient has adoptedthe Project Implementation Manual for the Project in form and substance acceptable to the Association | Due Date :31-Oct-2013

Finance Agreement :Steering CommitteeFinancing Agreement Reference 5.01(c) | Description :The Recipient has established theSteering Committee in accordance with the FA, with terms of reference, composition and resources acceptable to the Association |Due Date :31-Oct-2013

Finance Agreement :Subsidiary AgreementFinancing Agreement Reference 5.01 (a) | Description :The Subsidiary Agreement has beenexecuted on behalf of the Recipient and the Project Implementing Entity | Due Date :31-Oct-2013

Finance Agreement :Training Engineering SpecialistFinancing Agreement Reference I.A.2(c) | Description :The Recipient shallrecruit a Training Engineering Specialist with terms of reference, qualifications, and experience satisfactory to the Associationwithin 6 months of effectiveness. | Due Date :28-Apr-2014
